The paper deals with the problem of spectrum sensing in cognitive radio, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the effect of frequency offsets on the system, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY) and communication networks (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to spectrum sensing using a low complexity filter, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG).
